The paper focuses on developing a quality assessment approach for face recognition using deep learning, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The authors also mention the use of a commercial face recognition system, which could potentially fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and security and privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of a pre-trained face recognition network, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
